● Read TODO.md lines 33-33
  └ 1 line read

The bug requires `CONFIG_TRACE_IRQFLAGS` (enabled via `CONFIG_LOCKDEP`) to be observable — without it, `local_irq_enable()` and `raw_local_irq_enable()` are identical on x86. This is a tracing/RCU state ordering issue, not a scheduler logic bug reproducible through kSTEP's scheduler-level APIs. Skipping.

